gomodel:SYNGO_5268  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Mind Bomb-2 (MIB2) and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured rat hippocampal neurons showed partial co-localization.\n\nFigure 7: Mib2 associates with the NR2B subunit in the hippocampus.\n\"forskolin treatment resulted in an increase in NR2B phosphorylation (lanes 1 versus 2, top panel), and a corresponding increase in Mib2 co-immunoprecipitation with the NR2B subunit (lanes 1 versus 2, bottom panel). Similar results were obtained when KCl was added at the last 5 min of forskolin treatment to mimic brief neuronal stimulation (Fig. 7, lanes 3 versus 1 and 2). Together these results suggest that in the hippocampus, Mib2 binds NR2B in an activity-dependent manner.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"For the preparation of primary hippocampal neurons, newborn rats (P0) were decapitated, and hippocampi were dissected bilaterally. \"\n\nantibody:\n\"Affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal sera directed against a peptide sequence of mouse Mib2 (amino acids (aa) 429 - 443) was generated by New England Peptide (Gardner, MA) (Supplemental Fig. S1). Anti-Mib2 (mouse) antibodies were from Abnova (Taipei, Taiwan).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5268" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

